# Virtual Office World — Complete Headquarters Generation

Build a production-ready, pixel-art top-down virtual office headquarters using the existing Phaser + React (Vite) stack. The office must look like the headquarters of a successful tech company — inspired by Gather Town, WorkAdventure, and modern Silicon Valley startups.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **CEO Character Sprite**: There is already an excellent pixel-art CEO spritesheet at [player_spritesheet.png](file:///d:/College/Projects/AI%20BUSSINESS/git_hub_branch/virtual%20office/virtual-office-web/public/assets/player_spritesheet.png) (dark suit, white shirt, executive look — 5 frames × 4 directions). The current code uses a simple colored circle instead. This plan replaces the circle with the animated spritesheet.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Map Strategy**: The current map (`perfect-office.json`) is 80×50 tiles. The new headquarters requires ~100×80 tiles to fit all rooms. This will replace the existing map JSON. The existing tilesets (tileset1, tileset5_export, tileset6_export, tileset1-repositioning, Special_Zones) will be reused — they contain desks, chairs, monitors, plants, bookshelves, sofas, glass walls, and floor tiles needed for the office.

> [!WARNING]
> **Phaser Version**: The project uses Phaser 4.1.0. The spritesheet loading API may differ from Phaser 3. I will verify API compatibility and adapt accordingly.

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **NPC Employee Count**: How many AI workers / employees should walk around the office? I'm planning ~12-15 NPCs across departments (Product, Engineering, Design, AI) with simple patrol/random-walk behavior. Is this sufficient, or do you want more/fewer?

> [!IMPORTANT]  
